Package src.main

Class Commit

  • java.lang.Object
    • src.main.OmniObject
      • src.main.Commit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class Commit
extends OmniObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Commit is Omni's internal representation of a snapshot of a repository and its staged files at a particular point in time. As such, it is inclusive of metadata such as the prior commit, author, time of commit, and a commit message or log. The tree that it points to is the tracked repository.

      • getSHA1

        public java.lang.String getSHA1()
        Description copied from class: OmniObject
        Returns the SHA-1 hashcode associated with the OmniObject and its contents. For purposes of this project, we can assume that collisions are not going to be present. While this is traditionally a 40-character string, we prepend a 'B', 'T', or 'C' to the hashcode to differentiate between blobs, tree, and commits, respectively.
        Specified by:
        getSHA1 in class OmniObject
        Returns:
        SHA-1 encoding as a 41-character string.
